      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The expansion of the social safety net has created a significant disincentive to work by raising the cost of employment, particularly for low-income individuals. When government benefits are structured without adequate work requirements or earnings phase-outs, they effectively reduce the financial reward for taking a job, leading to lower labor force participation. This policy design encourages dependency and reduces the urgency to seek employment, which is a well-documented economic consequence of overly generous welfare programs.",
