      "content": "While automation and demographics are real trends, the primary driver of declining labor participation in recent years is the structural design of the safety net itself. These programs often create \"benefit cliffs\" where taking a job results in an immediate loss of income, making employment financially irrational for many low-wage workers. Consequently, the government's own policies are the most significant factor, not external economic shifts.",
